Caesarea was inhabited mixedly by Jews, heathens, and Samaritans. Hence some places in it were profane and un- clean to the Jews.

Of the various strifes and uproars between the Caesarean Greeks and Jews, in which the Jews always went by the worst, Josephus hath very much.
